8 March 2011As part of the buildup activities to the 2nd Biennial Substance Abuse Summit, the Inter-Ministerial Committee (IMC) on Anti-Substance Abuse held a special meeting on 9 March 2011 in Cape Town. On the agenda was the discussion on the work of the committee and the state of readiness for the forthcoming substance abuse summit that will take place from 15-17 March 2011 at the International Convention Centre in Durban.The Inter-Ministerial Committee will address a press conference on the outcomes of the meeting at a briefing to be held as follows:Date: 10 March 2011 (Thursday) Time: 10:00 Venue: Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Cape TownNOTE: There will be a video link-up at Room 153, Union Buildings, Pretoria RSVPs: Shadi Baloyi Cell: 076 946 7136Jaconia Kobue Cell: 073 021 1111Enquiries: Thapelo Sakoana Cell: 078 453 6750Abram Phahlamohlaka Cell: 082 928 6590 Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)